9:30 	Étude de cas : Thomas et al. 2004
		- Question de base
			Provide a first pass estimate of extinction probabilities associated with climate change scenarios for 2050. Estimate number of species that are "commited to extinction"
		- Méthodologie
			1 103 animal and plant species
			Estimate current distribution area
			Deux scénarios de dispersion
			Three methods to estimate extinctio based on the SAR
				method 1: changes in the summed distribution areas of all species
				method 2: average proportional loss of the distribution area
				method 3: considers the extinction risk of each species
				IUCN red list
		- Résultats principaux
			Species-level with max climate change extinction to be 21-32% (range of three methods) with universal dispersal and 38-	52% for no dispersal
			Projections vary with methods, organisms and areas of the world
			COmparison with extinctions from habitat losses. Some areas have larger climate change impacts, others are driven by land use	
		- Réactions ?
		- Réponse de Thuiller : Two additional sources of uncertainty
			- different SDMs. Differences may be as strong as between scenarios
			- using the SARs. Link between area reduction and extinction risk is questionable
			- conclusion : the range of extinction risks may even be wider than anticipated 
		- Quelle utilisation faire des prédictions ?
		- Comment faire différent 15 ans plus tard ?

