11:30	10 steps guide to ecological modeling

			Precisely define the objective
			Use theory to justify assumptions and manage complexity
			Schematize the model
			Make sure of mathematical rigor
			Proper interpretation of the model, limits and uncertainty 
			Debug the code AND the model
			Code properly and for others
			Keep a journal of model development and tests
			Run virtual experiments
			Model validation & updating
			Have in mind illustration of the results


			Modelling is a state of mind more than a technique. 



A model is a logical machine for deducing the latter from the former. If the model is correct, then, if you believe its assumptions, you must, as a matter of logic, also believe its conclusions. (Gunawardena, 2014. BMC Biology)
--> the whole is not necessarily the sum of the parts





